<task id="configure-mathflow-editor">
  <title>Configure the MathFlow Editor</title>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>The <i>MathFlow</i> Components product can replace the default <i>MathML</i> editor with a
        specialized <i>MathML</i> editor. You have to <xref
          href="http://www.dessci.com/en/products/mathflow/" scope="external" format="html">purchase
          a <term>MathFlow</term> Component from Design Science</xref> and configure it in <ph
          keyref="product"/> with the following procedure:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Install <i>MathFlow</i> by using the <i>Universal</i> installer (for versions prior to
          2.1, use the <i>MathFlow SDK</i>).</cmd>
      </step>
      <!--<step>
        <cmd>On Windows make sure there is a copy of the <i>FLEXlm</i> DLL, which is the file
            <filepath>[MathFlow-install-folder]/resources/windows/lmgr10.dll</filepath>, in a folder
          that is added to the <i>PATH</i> environment variable.</cmd>
      </step>-->
      <step>
        <cmd>Set the path to the <i>MathFlow</i> install folder <xref
            href="preferences-author-mathml.dita">in the <uicontrol>MathML</uicontrol>
            preferences page</xref>.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Set the path to the <i>MathFlow</i> license file <xref
            href="preferences-author-mathml.dita">in the <uicontrol>MathML</uicontrol>
            preferences page</xref>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>
            <fig>
              <title>Default MathFlow Editor</title>
              <image href="../img/sa_author_MathFlow_editor.png" placement="inline"/>
            </fig>
          </p>
        </info>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
